  <p class="hide">The apparition of these faces in the crowd:</p>
  <h1>What is melancholy?</h1>
  <img src="field.jpg" alt="Man in field on foggy day">
  <h2>Dark house, by which once more I stand<br>
    Here in the long unlovely street,<br>
  Doors, where my heart was used to beat.<br>
  So quickly, waiting for a hand,</h2>
  <h2>A hand that can be clasp'd no more—<br>
    Behold me, for I cannot sleep,<br>
    And like a guilty thing I creep<br>
    At earliest morning to the door.</h2>
  <img src="water.jpg" alt="Foggy ocean">
  <h1 class="left">He is not here; but far away</h1>
  <p>The noise of life begins again,<br>
    And ghastly thro' the drizzling rain<br>
    On the bald street breaks the blank day.</p>
  <img src="lettering.jpg" alt="hand lettering of poem">
  <img class="sunset" src="sunset.jpg" alt="Sunset on a road">
  <h2>“And the days are not full enough<br>
    And the nights are not full enough<br>
    And life slips by like a field mouse.<br>
    Not shaking the grass.”</h2>
  <p>But -<br>
    These days it feels<br>
    The days are much too full.<br>
    As if life will just keep going and going,<br>
    Mercilessly,<br>
    Without end.</p>
  <p>Life is crawling. Life is dawdling.</p>
  <p>A desolate march forward with no
    Purpose,<br>
    And an unspoken rule that one must<br>
    Keep on.<br>
    Despite everything.<br>
    Despite unlivableness.<br>
    But we must keep going on and on.</p>
  <p>On and on, so that others<br>
    We know<br>
    Can keep on.</p>
  <p>And they will keep on for us.</p>
  <img src="treestumps.png" alt="Tree stumps poking through fog">
  <div class="blackbg">
    <p class="hidden">I have been one acquainted with the night.<br>
      I have walked out in rain—and back in rain.<br>
      I have outwalked the furthest city light.<br>
      I have looked down the saddest city lane.</p>
    <h1 class="white">What is my melancholy?</h1>
